The Sultan of Sokoto and president-general, Nigeria Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs (NSCIA) Muhammad
Sa’ad Abubakar III, yesterday endorsed community policing just as he promised continued support from the traditional institution towards attaining the desired objectives. The Sultan, who divulged that the traditional institution would uphold and respect all principles governing the operations of the community policing policy in the states, added that the degree of insecurity lately in Nigeria
calls for all hands to be on deck. Speaking on behalf of the traditional leaders when the state commissioner of Police, Ibrahim Ka’oje inaugurated
Sokoto South (Metro)Community Policing Area Command committee at the Sultan’s palace, the respected
religious cum traditional leader tasked everybody to be security conscious and give vital information to relevant
authorities.